Firstly, the starving kids were not in the studio that day of shooting.  Secondly, they are running a business... Serious implications about exploitation of starving children for youtube hits...  and, I'm pretty sure the primary viewership is looking for a "feel good" experience from their channel and not "aw, this is both nice and horribly depressing at the same time."  I don't think that's what they're going for.

It would be nice to see bon appetite sponsoring a food drive or fund raiser for feeding starving children around the world... But, I really don't want them pandering for money from me...
